A 60-year-old man, Godwin Anukwa, was yesterday arraigned before an Ikeja Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly assaulting his daughter, 8, inserted his finger in her private parts. The defendant pleaded not guilty to count charge of child defilement before Chief Magistrate Yewande Aje-Afunwa. Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Peter Nwangwu said the defendant committed the offence in March at Airport Estate, Isheri, Lagos. The defendant, according to him, was arrested after the case was reported. Chief Magistrate Aje-Afunwa granted the defendant N500,000 bail with two sureties each in the like sum. The sureties, she said, should be gainfully employed, adding that they must show evidence of tax payments to the Lagos State Government. One of them must be related to the defendant, the magistrate added. She adjourned till July 17. Also yesterday, a tanker driver, John Mathias, 45, was arraigned before the court for allegedly stealing diesel oil valued at N17.8 million, belonging to Haido Oil and Gas. The defendant is standing trial on a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing Nwangwu said the defendant committed the offence on January 10 at Ibeto Oil and Gas Depot and Integrated Oil and Gas at Apapa, Lagos. He alleged that the defendant conspired with others at large to steal the product. Nwangwu alleged that the defendant stole the 90,000 litres of diesel loaded in two trucks marked SMK 462 XY and KTU 79 XM. He said the defendant and his other accomplice absconded with the diesel to an unknown destination. The defendant was later arrested durign investigation. Chief Magistrate Aje-Afunwa granted the defendant N5 million bail. She ordered that the defendant must provide two sureties in the like sum, one of whom must be a property owner in Lagos. 